she takes issue with two things.
Number one.

34
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:39,737
Ki-baek and Ms. On Woo-ju.
They were already a couple

35
00:04:39,821 --> 00:04:42,699
before we started filming
Couple's Paradise.

36
00:04:42,782 --> 00:04:44,075
Hold tight!

37
00:04:44,784 --> 00:04:47,829
And that's how Song Ki-baek,
who wasn't well-known, got cast

38
00:04:47,912 --> 00:04:49,372
thanks to the head writer.

39
00:04:49,455 --> 00:04:51,582
Your daughter has that much influence?

40
00:04:51,666 --> 00:04:52,625
Influence? No.

41
00:04:52,709 --> 00:04:55,878
I ask for a celebrity's autograph,
and she says it's abuse of power--

42
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:58,256
-Mom. I didn't do that.
-You did!

43
00:04:58,756 --> 00:05:00,341
Now, number two.

44
00:05:00,425 --> 00:05:04,053
Ms. On got jealous of
her boyfriend's love interest in the show…

45
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:07,140
On Woo-ju revealed her ambition
to become a celebrity,

46
00:05:07,682 --> 00:05:11,227
kicked Choi Yu-yeong off the show,
and took her place.

47
00:05:12,603 --> 00:05:13,813
Interesting.

48
00:05:14,522 --> 00:05:16,733
First, let me go talk to Min Cho-hui.

49
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:20,320
You can't. She's already gone to France.

50
00:05:20,403 --> 00:05:21,237
What?

51
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:23,948
She screwed us over and fled.

52
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:27,869
Should we go to France to find her?

53
00:05:27,952 --> 00:05:29,871
Let me get the facts straight.

54
00:05:29,954 --> 00:05:33,333
Your relationship began
after Couple's Paradise,

55
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:36,627
and the person who drove off
Yu-yeong was Cho-hui. Correct?

56
00:05:36,711 --> 00:05:38,254
-Yes.
-Yes, that's right.

57
00:05:39,088 --> 00:05:43,468
Well, then, should we think
about how to argue this?

58
00:05:44,052 --> 00:05:48,806
We can argue all we want,
but there's no proof.

59
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:51,392
Would that work?

60
00:05:51,476 --> 00:05:53,478
What else then? We do nothing?

61
00:05:53,561 --> 00:05:55,271
Man, I don't know.

62
00:05:55,980 --> 00:05:59,025
What if we're just giving people
another form of entertainment?

63
00:06:19,587 --> 00:06:22,632
Man, this is completely untrue.

64
00:06:25,718 --> 00:06:27,011
What are you up to?

65
00:06:27,887 --> 00:06:28,930
Why'd you make rice balls?

66
00:06:30,598 --> 00:06:31,641
They're combat rations.

67
